    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The application is designed as a single-page, scrolling interactive portfolio. This structure allows recruiters to either get a quick overview by scrolling, or deep-dive into specific areas using the sticky navigation. Key sections are: a hero intro, a visual "Key Achievements" dashboard to immediately showcase impact, an interactive timeline for work experience to reduce clutter, dynamic charts for skills to visualize proficiency, and organized cards for certifications. This non-linear, thematic approach is more user-friendly and engaging than a static document, allowing a potential employer to quickly access the most relevant information for their needs. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Professional Summary -> Goal: Inform -> Viz: Hero text block -> Interaction: None -> Justification: A clean, strong opening statement.
        - Key Achievements -> Goal: Impress -> Viz: Dashboard-style stat cards (HTML/CSS) -> Interaction: Hover effects -> Justification: Immediately highlights major, quantifiable accomplishments to grab attention.
        - Experience -> Goal: Organize/Inform -> Viz: Accordion/Timeline (HTML/JS) -> Interaction: Click to expand details -> Justification: Keeps the main view clean and allows users to explore roles they are most interested in without being overwhelmed.
        - Skills -> Goal: Compare/Inform -> Viz: Horizontal Bar Charts (Chart.js Canvas) -> Interaction: Tooltips on hover -> Justification: Visually represents expertise levels in a far more engaging way than a simple list.
        - Certifications -> Goal: Organize/Inform -> Viz: Icon-based grid cards (HTML/CSS) -> Interaction: Hover effects -> Justification: Thematic grouping with icons makes this section easily scannable and visually appealing.
        - CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
